## Coming Off Day 8

Yesterday I spent time with PCI DSS — a framework that is highly prescriptive and tells you almost exactly what to do. Today I moved into something quite different: **ISO/IEC 27001**, which is far less about checklists and far more about building a system for managing security over time. The contrast between the two was genuinely useful, and I came away from today with a much clearer sense of why different frameworks exist and when each one is the right tool.

